      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden, ¶ 1/10/72 ¶  ¶ If you will be so kind, dear Major Purchase, ¶ i.e. Purchas. ¶  to submit to the Board of trustees my proposition of taking again charge of the plants in the old ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.10.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Albert Purchas</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Letter book 2, no. 79, Melbourne General Cemetery.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by A. Purchas: 'Read 9-10-72 A.P.'.</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1/10/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you will be so kind, dear Major Purchase,<seg style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">i.e. Purchas.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg> to submit to the Board of trustees my proposition of taking again charge of the plants in the old Cemetery, I shall gladly attend to their order, before the hot weather causes a ruin among the plants and before the season of sorting annuals is lost.<seg style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">No record of such an offer by M has been found. See however A. Purchas to M, 4 September 1872 (in this edition as 72-09-04b), and A. Purchas to M, 11 October 1872.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
